tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ProteinInteractionNetworks (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   protein_id_1 INT,
   protein_id_2 INT,
   interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
   interaction_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Protein (protein_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
protein_name VARCHAR(255),
protein_type VARCHAR(50),
protein_sequence TEXT)

CREATE TABLE Interaction (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
protein_id1 INT,
protein_id2 INT,
interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
interaction_strength FLOAT,
FOREIGN KEY (protein_id1) REFERENCES Protein(protein_id),
FOREIGN KEY (protein_id2) REFERENCES Protein(protein_id))

CREATE TABLE Pathway (pathway_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
pathway_name VARCHAR(255),
pathway_description TEXT)

CREATE TABLE Protein (protein_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
protein_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
protein_sequence TEXT)

CREATE TABLE Interaction (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
interaction_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
interaction_description TEXT,
protein1_id INT NOT NULL,
protein2_id INT NOT NULL,
FOREIGN KEY (protein1_id) REFERENCES Protein(protein_id),
FOREIGN KEY (protein2_id) REFERENCES Protein(protein_id))

CREATE TABLE Pathway (pathway_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
pathway_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
pathway_description TEXT)

CREATE TABLE Pathway_Protein (pathway_id INT,
protein_id INT,
PRIMARY KEY (pathway_id, protein_id),
FOREIGN KEY (pathway_id) REFERENCES Pathway(pathway_id),
FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES Protein(protein_id))
